---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import PageHeader from '../components/PageHeader.astro';

const sections = [
{ id: 'retreat', label: 'Retreat 2026' },
{ id: 'where', label: 'Where and when' },
{ id: 'who', label: 'Who is it for?' },
{ id: 'overview', label: 'Overview' },
{ id: 'outcomes', label: 'Workshop outcomes' },
{ id: 'apply', label: 'How to apply' },
];
---

<Layout title="Retreat 2026" currentDomain="retreat-2026">
  <div class="skills-framework">
    <PageHeader title="Retreat 2026" />
    <div class="sticky-subnav">
      <div class="subdomain-tabs" id="section-tabs">
        {sections.map(s => (
        <button class="tab subdomain-tab" data-section={s.id}>
          {s.label}
        </button>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="scroll-area" id="scroll-area">
      <div class="page-container">
        <h2 id="retreat">Retreat 2026</h2>
        <p>
          Applications are open to attend a <b> fully funded technical skills residential training workshop </b> to
          develop skills to pursue a career supporting research organisations to design, build and maintain secure data
          environments.
        </p>
        <p>
          This workshop will focus on developing an understanding of the Research Technical Professional role and the
          skills needed to design, build and maintain Secure Data Environments (SDEs).
        </p>
        <article class="card glass--soft">
          <div class="card-header">
            <div id="where" class="card-info">
              <h2>Where and when</h2>
              <div class="info-row"><strong>Location:</strong> The Rookery Hotel, Crewe</div>
              <div class="info-row"><strong>Dates:</strong> 11-13 November 2026</div>
              <div class="info-row"><strong>Arrival:</strong> by 3pm 11 November</div>
              <div class="info-row"><strong>Departure:</strong> 3pm 13 November</div>
            </div>

          </div>
          <hr />
          <div>
            <div id="who" class="card-info">
              <h2>Who is it for?</h2>

              <p>Individuals currently supporting research organisations to design, build and maintain secure data
                environments, or individuals that have a desire to work in this area in the future. Attendees should be
                at an early stage of personal development in this area and might be from a range of backgrounds
                including technical, professional services or research/ academic. Attendees could include:</p>
              <ul>
                <li>Recent graduates from courses in computer science, data science, informatics or related disciplines;
                </li>

                <li>Junior or trainee technical professionals working with secure data environments in a research
                  setting, for example: platform, data and DevOps engineers; </li>

                <li>Those with Research Support Roles (e.g., RSEs, System Administrators, and IT Solution Architects)
                </li>

                <li>Research technical professionals in other fields looking to pivot into research data infrastructure.
                </li>
              </ul>
              <p>Prior knowledge required: All attendees should have some experience with software development or
                scripting, understand basic terminal commands and have some experience with version control systems
                including Git. </p>
            </div>
            <hr />
            <div id="overview" class="card-info">
              <h2>Overview</h2>
              <ol>
                <li>Architecting Secure Data Environments: Core Principles and Practical Implementation As the UK
                  increasingly relies on Secure Data Environments (SDEs) to analyse sensitive research datasets, the
                  ability to design and maintain these systems has become a vital capability. This workshop offers a
                  guided, hands-on introduction to Trusted Research Environments (TREs) for individuals looking to build
                  their expertise in this specialized area. </li>



                <li> Foundations & Architecture: We will begin by exploring the specific needs of secure research data
                  services and the essential skills required to operate as a Research Technical Professional (RTP). You
                  will learn the core architectural principles that govern SDEs, focusing on data security, access
                  control, and scalable compute.</li>



                <li> Practical Implementation
                  <p>To ensure you gain practical experience without getting bogged down in initial setup, the technical
                    portion of the workshop is heavily scaffolded. You will be provided with a foundational, Azure-based
                    codebase to act as a working demonstration of our taught principles. Throughout the exercise, you
                    will:</p>

                  <ul>
                    <li>Adapt and modify the core codebase to meet specific requirements. </li>
                    <li>Discuss and defend your design choices, linking them directly to the RTP skills framework. </li>

                    <li>Learn how to translate these specific Azure implementations into equivalent architectures for
                      AWS, GCP, or on-premises environments. </li>

                    <li>Participants will conclude the session equipped with a working knowledge of SDE architecture and
                      the necessary resources to pursue independent, follow-up learning. </li>

                    <li>We will also run parallel sessions on different models for implementation and related skills or
                      technologies. These will include Kubernetes, data engineering and AI. </li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
              </ol>
            </div>
            <hr />

            <div id="outcomes" class="card-info">
              <h2>Workshop outcomes</h2>
              <p>Attendees will have participated in a collaborative, expert-led event that included: </p>
              <ul>
                <li><strong>Expert Insight:</strong> Direct training from field experts on the evolving standards for UK
                  research data services. Includes understanding the research technical professional pathway and
                  opportunities within research and academia and its role in enabling Team Science and collaborative
                  ways of working. </li>

                <li><strong>Practical Deployment:</strong> Hands-on experience adapting and deploying secure, scalable
                  research frameworks. Developing practical technical skills training and development supporting trusted
                  research environments (TREs). </li>

                <li><strong>Architectural Translation:</strong> Skills to move beyond a single cloud provider, applying
                  security controls across different cloud environments, data services and research tools. </li>

                <li><strong>Competency Alignment:</strong> A clear understanding of how to document and demonstrate
                  technical work against the RTP professional standards. </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <hr />
            <div id="agenda" class="card-info">
              <h2>Indicative agenda (subject to change)</h2>

              <h3>Wednesday 10th November</h3>
              <table class="agenda-table">
                <thead>
                  <tr>
                    <th>Time</th>
                    <th>Session</th>
                  </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                  <tr>
                    <td>14.00</td>
                    <td>Arrival</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td>Afternoon</td>
                    <td>Introductory Session</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td>Evening</td>
                    <td>Free-time<br />Dinner with invited speaker<br />Free-time / Social activity (optional)</td>
                  </tr>
                </tbody>
              </table>

              <h3>Thursday 11th November</h3>
              <table class="agenda-table">
                <thead>
                  <tr>
                    <th>Time</th>
                    <th>Session</th>
                  </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                  <tr>
                    <td>Morning</td>
                    <td><strong>Session 1:</strong> Icebreaker<br />Introduction to Team Science and The RTP Competency Framework<br /><br /><strong>Session 2:</strong> Overview of Trusted Research Environments (TREs and SDEs)</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td>Afternoon</td>
                    <td>Lunch<br /><br /><strong>Session 3 —</strong> Technical Hand-on Workshop: Building and Modifying a TRE</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td>Evening</td>
                    <td>Dinner with invited speaker<br />Free-time / Social activity (optional)</td>
                  </tr>
                </tbody>
              </table>

              <h3>Friday 12th November</h3>
              <table class="agenda-table">
                <thead>
                  <tr>
                    <th>Time</th>
                    <th>Session</th>
                  </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                  <tr>
                    <td>Morning</td>
                    <td>Icebreaker/wakeup exercise<br />Parallel Sessions – Specialist topics</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td>Afternoon</td>
                    <td>Lunch<br /><br />15.00 - Refreshments & Close</td>
                  </tr>
                </tbody>
              </table>
            </div>
            <hr />
            <div id="apply" class="card-info">
              <h2>How to apply</h2>
              <p><a href="#">Click here</a> to go to our Google forms application form.</p>
               <p>We are using a short application process rather than first-come, first-served registration. This helps us: 
                  <ul>
                    <li><strong>Manage demand:</strong> this is expected to be highly competitive and with limited spaces we wish to enable equal opportunity to apply </li>

                    <li><strong>Allocate places fairly:</strong> with a balanced mix of participants </li>

                    <li><strong>Support those who will benefit most:</strong> from the residential experience </li>
                  </ul>
               </p>

 

                <p>We encourage ALL applications at this stage so if this event speaks to you, we welcome you to apply.</p>

 

<p>All applications will be reviewed and applicants will be sorted into successful / waiting list / unsuccessful and applicants informed.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>

<script define:vars={{ sections }}>
  window._pageSections = sections;
</script>
<script>
  import { initScrollSync } from '../scripts/scrollSync.js';
  initScrollSync({ sections: window._pageSections });
</script>